article.headline: Wichita State 86, Texas Southern 54
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Karon Bradley scored 19 points and Paul Miller had 14 points and 15 rebounds as Wichita State rolled to a 86-54 victory over Texas Southern Sunday in the Padre Island Tournament. Wichita State (2-0) held the Tigers scoreless for the first 5:35 and without a field goal for the first 8:21. By that time, the Shockers led 18-4 en route to a 36-11 halftime lead. Wichita State stretched the lead to 36 points in the second half. Courtnay Brown hit three 3-pointers for Texas Southern (1-1) and finished with 11 points. Sean Walker had 14 points. Both teams struggled to control the ball, combining for 33 turnovers. Kyle Wilson scored 15 points for Wichita State, including 9-for-9 from the foul line. As a team, the Shockers hit 83 percent of their free throws. Wichita State also out-rebounded the Tigers 55-29.
